## New bin launchers

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash

cd "$(dirname "$0")/../ruby/04_api_client"
bundle exec ruby examples/example.rb
```

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
cd "$(dirname "$0")/../python/04_api_client"
uv run python examples/example.py
```

Both need `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (or whichever provider's key) in the
environment to run for real — sourced from the repo root's gitignored
`.env` for the live-verification runs (see the acceptance-test section
above), not baked into the launcher scripts themselves (Ruby's `Config`
only ever reads `.boukensha/.env` — no new config-loading precedence is
being invented here).

